2 elect to permanently waive future participation in the retirement plan and the
3 retiree health program and maintain that employee's retirement status. An
4 employee making this election is not required to make any future employee
5 contributions to the public employees retirement system nor is the employee's
6 employer required to make any further contributions on behalf of that employee.
7 d. An employee eligible for normal retirement who accepts a retirement benefit
8 under this chapter and subsequently becomes employed with the same
9 participating employer the employee was employed with at the time the employee
10 retired under this chapter may not participate in the retirement plan or the retiree
11 health program and may maintain that employee's retirement status if the
12 employee is appointed by an elected state official to an unclassified state position
13 for the duration of the elected official's term until a successor is appointed.
14 SECTION 2. RETROACTIVE APPLICATION. This Act applies retroactively to
15 December 14, 2024.
16 SECTION 3. EMERGENCY. This Act is declared to be an emergency measure.
